author: Jack
text:
Very nice and clean environment will be how I describe this AF.
Cleaning cloths and solution are available everywhere.
Lots of pigeon holes at the rack and also in changing room and machine area do you do not need to walk too far.
Changing area is clean as well.
Everyone just go about doing their own stuff without much hoggers or chatters which is good.
Most of the weights are in their rightful place so that's gym etiquette here.
Improvements can be made to the Aircon which feels warm, and water cooler isn't really that cold either I had my post workout in room temperature water. Maybe just a bit more room to manoeuvre in between the stations will be better if some adjustment can be made.

author: hello gmail
text:
I've been going to Anytime Fitness Bedok 85 for the past 6 months and it's been a fantastic experience. The gym is always clean, well-organized, and equipped with everything you need, from free weights to cardio machines.

The workers are knowledgeable and always willing to help, whether you're new to fitness or more advanced.

One of the biggest pluses for me is how welcoming and inclusive the environment is. No judgment, just people working toward their goals.

Highly recommend to anyone looking for a quality gym with a supportive atmosphere!

author: rohan james
text:
if you see some of the reviews previously, there were some comments on the flooring issues under the previous management. the floor was caved in for months, mirrors were cracked for years, yet the previous management never did anything.

new management came in and worked on those. i also sounded out some comments about the new layout of the gym, and the assistant manager, hakim came over to hear my concerns and to ensure that the new management is not just cognisant, but genuinely invested in the experience of the their members.

still not a fan of the new layout haha but i am very impressed with the new management and trust that they will keep the gym in great condition. shout out to all three hakims but especially the hakim i spoke to

As someone who‚Äôs new to the area, I couldn‚Äôt have asked for a better introduction. Yulun‚Äôs tour was not only informative but also filled with genuine enthusiasm. ‚≠êÔ∏è State-of-the-Art Equipment: Step into our sleek facility and discover a haven of cutting-edge fitness equipment. From cardio machines to free weights, every workout enthusiast will find their perfect match to crush their goals.

‚≠êÔ∏è Expert Guidance: Our team of dedicated trainers are here to support and motivate you every step of the way. Whether you're a beginner or a seasoned pro, they'll tailor personalized workout plans to ensure maximum results.

‚≠êÔ∏è Wellness Hub: Elevate your fitness journey with our range of wellness amenities, including showers, lockers, and a cozy lounge area. Refresh, recharge, and leave feeling rejuvenated after each session.

‚≠êÔ∏è Special Events: Stay tuned for our exciting lineup of fitness challenges, workshops, and social gatherings. Get ready to sweat, smile, and create lasting memories with the Anytime Fitness family!

Don't just dream about your fitness goals ‚Äì make them a reality at Anytime Fitness, Bedok. Join us today and embark on a journey to a healthier, happier you! üí™üèãÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

text:
I recently had the pleasure of experiencing exceptional service from the staff, YUDA at Anytime Fitness, and I must say, it exceeded my expectations. From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with warm smiles and genuine enthusiasm from the staff members. They were incredibly knowledgeable about the facility and its offerings, taking the time to answer all of my questions and provide valuable guidance on achieving my fitness goals.

What truly stood out to me was their willingness to go above and beyond to ensure I felt comfortable and supported during my workouts. Whether it was assisting with equipment setup, offering helpful workout tips, or simply providing words of encouragement, the staff at Anytime Fitness made me feel like a valued member of the community.

Additionally, their commitment to cleanliness and safety measures was evident throughout the facility, which provided me with peace of mind during these uncertain times.

Overall, I cannot speak highly enough of the staff at Anytime Fitness. Their dedication to customer satisfaction and passion for promoting health and wellness truly sets them apart. I highly recommend this gym to anyone looking for a positive and empowering fitness experience.

author: harmony
text:
great customer service! staff were helpful and quick when signing up for membership

update: you can probably get a cheaper membership rate at other outlets during the promotion period, no need to get from 85. their freezing fee is a whopping $8/week which adds up to $32/month. more than $1/day for something you are not even using. i froze for 3 months and the price is already on par with the price of actually using their facilities for one month. other gyms' freezing fee is cheaper than this like $20/month. i tried to change my home gym to the cheaper one the month prior to my freezing but the membership home gym wont change no matter what i do. they state that the home gym will be transferred by the system automatically based on which gym you visit more within the month. for one month i tapped mostly at another gym, but my home gym is still 85. my sister did not even go to 85 for one whole month, yet her home gym is still at 85. i think its quite ridiculous. just sign up at a cheaper gym and use the 85 gym instead.

author: Gillian Guo
text:
Cleanliness: 5/5
Everything is clean and very new. What i like is there is always a cleaner helping to clean up the gym every now and then. And i love the lemongrass scent you guys used in the gym. Very refreshing.

Equipment: 4/5
The equipment in my opinion is a little limited due to space but it is generally okay (could be abit of an issue during peak hours). They are very very new by the way.

Shower/Toilet: 4.5/5
Also another thumbs up for the showers - omg i love the shampoo and shower gels you guys supply. They have separate female and male toilets; 2 unisex showers, and a small dressing room with dyson hairdryer! I personally thought there should at least be a common washing basin.

Lighting: 5/5
Very soft lighting used. Very happy with this ambience lighting. I dont generally like super bright white lights. But since this was well planned out - it gives the user a cozy and comfortable feeling.

Booking of class: 3/5
I have to say its a hit and miss. Due to the small space. I dont think they can think in that many people for each class. And theres once the staff overlooked my request for the booking of yoga slot. But hey it can be improved. 6pm class timing is abit odd especially for people who work. So a minus for this. Would really appreciate if there is a weekday 8pm class or an early morning class on a Sat.

Can i ask that if you guys gonna add another outlet - use exactly the same stuff you have here BUT with bigger space. i will tell u its gonna be a bang!

Gym wise: The smell of lemongrass welcomes you as soon as you step in. Clean and well maintained. Varied machines and ample lockers provided as well. There are 2 showers, 1 changing room and separate toilets for Males & Females. There is a watercooler as well.

PT sessions: Conducted within your limits, varied and safe. Tarmizi allows the session to flow effortlessly. He is excellent in making things simple for layman like me to understand. All my progress is tracked using their dedicated technical platforms.

Engage in their 1 hr-PT sessions if you would want a guided and safe exercise journey.
